Step 1: Calculate the Quick Assets by summing the readily available liquid assets (excluding inventory):

 • Cash on Hand = 4,560,423.24  
 • Bank Deposits = 3,655,000.00  
 • Interest Receivable = 10,051.66  
 • Accounts Receivable = 1,133,414.13  

Quick Assets = 4,560,423.24 + 3,655,000.00 + 10,051.66 + 1,133,414.13  
            = 9,358,889.03

Step 2: Extract the Total Current Liabilities from the balance sheet:
 • Total Current Liabilities = 1,124,588.25

Step 3: Compute the Quick Ratio:
 Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
       = 9,358,889.03 / 1,124,588.25  
       ≈ 8.32

Step 4: For the Net Profit Margin, use the income statement figures:
 • Net Profit = 1,163,543.07  
 • Total Revenue = 5,991,764.34

Step 5: Compute the Net Profit Margin:
 Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
        = (1,163,543.07 / 5,991,764.34) × 100%  
        ≈ 19.42%

Thus, the final result is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "8.32",
    "Net Profit Margin": "19.42%"
  }
}
